  "local_port": 36404,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "If you're receiving a persistent \"Dock connected\" notification on your Android device, it usually indicates that your phone is detecting a dock accessory, such as a charging dock or a docking station. Here are several steps you can take to resolve the issue:\n\n1. **Disconnect Accessories**: Ensure that any dock or accessory is properly disconnected. Sometimes, it might not have been disconnected fully. Physically unplug any charging or docking stations you may have.\n\n2. **Go to Settings**:\n   - Open the **Settings** app on your Android device.\n   - Look for **Connected devices** or **Connections**.\n   - Check if a dock is listed there and, if so, disconnect or forget it.\n\n3. **Restart Your Device**: Sometimes, a simple restart can help clear temporary glitches. Power off your device, wait a few seconds, and then turn it back on.\n\n4. **Check for Software Updates**: Ensure your device is running the latest version of Android:\n   - Open **Settings**.\n   - Scroll down to **System** or **About phone**.\n   - Look for **Software update** and check for any available updates.\n\n5. **Clear Cache of the Dock Service**:\n   - Go to **Settings > Apps**.\n   - Tap the three dots (or \"Show system\" if needed) and look for **DockService** or any similar service.\n   - Clear the cache and storage for that service.\n\n6. **Safe Mode**: Boot your device into Safe Mode to see if a third-party app is causing the issue.\n   - Press and hold the power button until the power menu appears.\n   - Tap and hold the **Power off** option until you see the option to reboot in **Safe mode**.\n   - Tap **OK** to reboot. If the notification disappears in Safe Mode, it may be caused by a third-party app.\n\n7. **Factory Reset** (as a last resort): If nothing else works, you can reset your phone to factory settings. Remember to back up any important data first:\n   - Go to **Settings > System > Reset options > Erase all data (factory reset)**.\n\nIf the problem persists after trying these steps, there may be a hardware issue with the device itself. In that case, you may want to contact customer support or visit a repair center for further assistance.",
